\f0\fs24 <!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\fs28 A 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 spectacle blind flange
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28  is shaped like a pair of glasses or 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::3>
\f1\fs28 spectacles
\f0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::3>
\f1\fs28   <mdash/> hence the name. One half is open to allow flow through during normal operation and the other side is solid to block flow and secure the system for maintenance.  The two halves are separated by a spacer with a hole for one flange bolt. They are generally installed in the piping system permanently. \
\pard\sb40\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

