\f1\fs28 An 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 orifice flange
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28  is used in conjunction with a differential pressure sensor to measure the rate of flow in the pipe. \
An 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 orifice
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28  is a hole through which fluid may pass. When fluid flows through an orifice it creates a pressure drop, which is measured by the pressure sensor.  The flow rate through the orifice is proportional to the square root of the pressure drop and can be calculated knowing the orifice diameter. \
\pard\sb40\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

