\f1\fs28 The orifice flange assembly consists of a pair of flanges containing 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 pressure taps
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28 , an 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 orifice plate
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28 ,  
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 jacking screws
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28  and the normal gaskets, nuts and bolts.  The orifice plate has a precision hole (the 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\b\fs28 orifice
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs28 ) drilled through its center, and a tab stamped with the hole diameter.  Taps are threaded holes drilled through the flanges where the differential pressure sensor is connected.  The jacking screws are used to spread the flanges when replacing the orifice plate.\

